  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Traditionally the watertightness of urethrovesical anastomosis after robotic radical
      prostatectomy is controlled by cystogram. However, clinical observations and one previous
      study showed that patients with anastomotic leakage have red coloured urine. If the
      investigators can verify this finding, the most of the cystograms can be avoided. In this
      study the investigators estimate urine colour after cystogram and take a picture from urine
      collecting pag. Later on the pictures are digitally analyzed and compared to cystogram
      finding.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
